    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 2002 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) is powered by the 3.6L M96 flat-six engine, featuring VarioCam Plus for an optimized power band and producing 320 hp. The longitudinal 6-speed manual transaxle offers precise gear engagement with a firm clutch take-up. Crucially, this unit has undergone an IMS bearing retrofit and a Rear Main Seal (RMS) replacement, addressing key longevity concerns. The suspension maintains its factory-spec MacPherson strut front and multi-link rear configuration, providing excellent lateral stability and mechanical grip. Braking performance is sharp, utilizing four-piston monoblock calipers over vented, cross-drilled rotors. The exterior retains its aerodynamic profile with minor road-going patina, while the cabin's leather and switchgear remain functional and intact. Recent maintenance includes a cooling system pressure test and a fresh fill of high-zinc synthetic oil to ensure optimal lubrication of the valvetrain.",
      "price": 31500.0,
